CLASS:: VoxProxy
SUMMARY:: extract one labelled voice from upstream VoxMulti output
CATEGORIES:: VoxBox>Patching
RELATED:: Classes/VoxRouter, Classes/VoxRoute, Classes/VoxMulti

DESCRIPTION::
VoxProxy is a small node used by VoxRouter. It asks its input for output, selects one key and optionally applies a transform function.

CLASSMETHODS::

METHOD:: new
Create a proxy with key and optional transform.

INSTANCEMETHODS::

METHOD:: out
Return the selected Vox from upstream output.

EXAMPLES::

code::
proxy = VoxProxy(\tenor);
routerInput >>> proxy;
proxy.out;
::

SECTION:: Deficiencies

list::
## Missing-key behaviour returns nil without much context.
::

SECTION:: Recommended improvements

list::
## Improve missing-key warnings.
## Add tests through VoxRouter rather than using this directly.
::
